<p>I have created a database <code>StudentInfo</code> and a table <code>Student</code> as follows:</p>  <pre><code>CREATE TABLE Student (      ID INT PRIMARY KEY IDENTITY(1,1),      Name nvarchar(255) ) </code></pre>  <p>and inserting the values:</p>  <pre><code>Insert Into Student Values ('Ashok')`  </code></pre>  <p>executing it 3 times, and </p>  <pre><code>Insert Into Student Values ('Achyut') </code></pre>  <p>executing it 2 times and total 5 rows of data are inserted into the table. </p>  <p>I want to display a result counting the result with the name having 'Ashok' &amp; 'Achyut'.</p>  <p>Generally for single values count in a column I use:</p>  <pre><code> SELECT Count(Name) AS NoOfStudentHavingNameAshok   FROM Student  WHERE Name = 'Ashok' </code></pre>  <p>but how to display the <code>NoOfStudentHavingNameAshok</code> &amp; <code>NoOfStudentHavingNameAchyut</code> what query should I run?</p>